        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/al-kafi:4:2:57:1",
        "text": [
          " كُلُّ صَوْمٍ يُفَرَّقُ إِلَّا ثَلَاثَةَ أَيَّامٍ فِي كَفَّارَةِ الْيَمِينِ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Abdullah Bin Sinan, ",
            "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup>, said, ‘Every Fast can be separated except for the three days regarding an expiation for the oath’."
          ],
          "en.sarwar": [
            "1. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from ‘ Abd Allah ibn Sinan who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘All fasts can lawfully be completed in different times except the fast which is as expiation for an oath.”’ "
          ]
        }
